Necromancers are dark casters specializing in entropy, death magic, and manipulation of spiritual residue.
They descend from the Entropy Scholars, independent practitioners who studied decay in institutional margins.
The Psionicist academies branded them heretics due to overlapping jurisdiction over mental residue surviving death.
Three core applications: sustaining departed spirits, drawing on residual spiritual energy, and weaponizing decay against living targets.
Combat role is offensive caster using entropic damage, life drain, and undead summoning.
The tradition developed independent transmission structures to persist through institutional pressure.
Necromancers operate in theological opposition to Clerics, who hold that spirit-sustaining destabilizes cosmic containment.
Training passes through independent lineages outside formal academic or religious institutions.
The Kinetimancer class builds on Necromancer entropy knowledge combined with Egomancer psionic methodology.
